<span class="displaytext"><strong>strategist david gergen compared mayor (candidate last)'s performance to reagan's.</strong> "i think (candidate full) won the night … [(candidate last)] seized a moment when ron paul sort of opened up this argument that maybe we had it coming, with 9/11 and (candidate last) just jumped into the debate, he disrupted the debate. to just say no, no, that's not right and i just don't agree with that. … [i]t was like a minor nashua moment when ronald reagan, you know, seized the microphone, there was a quality here about showing his sort of, not only his anger but strength that i think served him well tonight." (cnn's "anderson cooper 360," 5/15/07) <p><strong>strategist ed rollins, responding to gergen: "he looked very presidential … he had a ronald reagan moment, i think he had a (candidate full) moment."</strong> (cnn's "anderson cooper 360," 5/15/07) </p><p><strong>national review's katherine jean lopez: "unless something dramatic and not-characteristic-of tonight happens, rudy won."</strong> (katherine jean lopez, "i don't think you have to come back after the commercial," <a href="http://corner.nationalreview.com/post/?q=ztjjy2jim2yxyjjjnjq5njrkywrjzwywzdbknwi2ntm, 5/15/07">http://corner.nationalreview.com/post/?q=ztjjy2jim2yxyjjjnjq5njrkywrjzwywzdbknwi2ntm, 5/15/07</a>) </p><p><strong>national review's katherine jean lopez: "rudy references fort dix before 9/11.</strong> dealing with today, and the war that remains as real as it was five years ago. and shows he knows/doesn't have an interest in resting on his 'america's mayor' laurels." (katherine jean lopez, "classy, right," <a href="http://corner.nationalreview.com/post/?q=yzkxzjm2zjc5y2fjzjnhnzziyje2mwjlodhmmmuxmme">http://corner.nationalreview.com/post/?q=yzkxzjm2zjc5y2fjzjnhnzziyje2mwjlodhmmmuxmme</a>, 5/15/07) </p><p><strong>national review's ramesh ponnuru: "[rudy also wins] the coveted most-improved-performance medal."</strong> (ramesh ponnuru, " rudy also wins," <a href="